rmk:
A quite long recording of a displaying Common snipe. It isn't always easy to get it right because some birds draw pretty large circles. I'd chose to stand at its very edge so that I could get some decent quality when it was flying overhead. That also means that only 10% of its display is recorded clear, while the rest of the recording sounds more faint. I didn't want to cut out the long faint parts because then it wouldn't give the realistic image of these birds display flights as it is shown now.
At 1:42, you can hear the birds wingbeats as it is tumbling down towards me and my microphone because of an unkown reason. He might have had spotted a raptor? I don't know. Immediately after, he started to climb up again and continued his way. There is a river at a distance that cause some backgroundnoise. No filters used, original recording.
